  <brief_title>Use of the Atkins Diet for Children With Intractable Epilepsy: A Comparison of Daily Carbohydrate Limits</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Johns Hopkins University</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Johns Hopkins University</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study is designed to further investigate the use of a modified Atkins diet for children
      with intractable, daily seizures. It is a follow-up to a study recently completed by our
      institution. In this 6-month study, children will be randomized to either 10 or 20 grams of
      carbohydrate per day, then crossed over to the opposite amount at 3 months.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
